H3.text: Music in Australia could be found for thousands of years at a what. Corroboree

A4.text: Throughout Australia the word 'corroboree' embraces songs, dances, rallies and meetings of various kinds.

A5.text: The largest spectator event of the 19th century at the Adelaide Oval was the 'Grand Corroboree', performed by around 100 Aboriginal men and women from Point MacLeay mission and Yorke Peninsula on Friday 29 and Saturday 30 May 1885.
